{"timestamp": "2025-12-04 13:29:42.380404", "event": "llm_end", "text": "Submitted the diagnosis.\n\nSummary:\n- Anomaly detected: Yes\n- Faulty device: web_server_0 (10.200.0.3, web0.local)\n- Root cause: receiver_resource_contention\n\nRationale:\n- HTTP service on web_server_0 shows multi-second TCP handshake and TTFB delays, with LISTEN socket Recv-Q/Send-Q buildup, while ICMP and all other network components (OSPF, L2, DHCP/DNS) are healthy.\n- Problem reproduces locally within the server VLAN, excluding transit network issues and pointing to host-level contention or saturation on the receiving side (web_server_0).", "generation_info": {"finish_reason": "stop", "logprobs": null}, "invalid_tool_calls": [], "usage_metadata": {"input_tokens": 2452, "output_tokens": 135, "total_tokens": 2587, "input_token_details": {"audio": 0, "cache_read": 2304}, "output_token_details": {"audio": 0, "reasoning": 0}}}
